          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Should I use UUID v4 or v7 for my database primary keys?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">UUID v7 is generally recommended for database primary keys because it is time-ordered, which improves B-tree index performance and reduces page splits in databases like PostgreSQL and MySQL. UUID v4 values are randomly distributed and can cause index fragmentation at scale. UUID v1 also provides time-ordering but may leak the timestamp and potentially the machine identity. For modern applications, UUID v7 offers the best balance of performance, privacy, and sortability.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 bg-canvas">
          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Is this UUID generator free to use?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">Yes, this UUID generator is completely free to use. There are no usage limits, no registration required, and no premium tiers. All UUID generation happens locally in your browser using the Web Crypto API &mdash; no data is sent to any server. You can generate as many UUIDs as you need for personal projects, commercial applications, or any other use.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 bg-canvas">
          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What is a GUID? Are UUID and GUID the same?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">GUID stands for Globally Unique Identifier. It is Microsoft's implementation of the UUID standard. Conceptually and structurally, they are the same 128-bit identifiers, though Microsoft tools traditionally write them in uppercase and sometimes wrap them in curly braces.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 bg-canvas">
          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>How does the Web Crypto API generate random bits?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">The Web Crypto API uses cryptographically secure pseudorandom number generators (CSPRNG) provided by the host operating system (such as /dev/urandom on Unix systems). This is much more secure than Math.random(), preventing predictability in production systems.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 bg-canvas">
          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What is the chance of a UUID collision?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">For UUID v4, you would need to generate 1 billion UUIDs per second for about 85 years to have a 50% chance of a single collision. For UUID v7, because the first 48 bits represent a timestamp, collisions can only happen if two identical random parts are generated within the exact same millisecond, which is highly improbable.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 bg-canvas">
          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Why is UUID v7 sortable?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">UUID v7 stores a 48-bit Unix timestamp in its most significant bits (at the beginning of the string). Since values generated later will have a larger timestamp, they naturally sort lexicographically after earlier ones, matching creation order.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 bg-canvas">
          <button type="button" class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Can I generate UUIDs in bulk?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">Yes. This generator lets you generate up to 500 UUIDs at a time. You can choose the format (standard, uppercase, no hyphens, CSV, JSON array) and copy or download them instantly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Tools -->
    <section class="mt-20 pt-16 border-t border-hairline">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-mute mb-6">Related Developer Tools</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-5 gap-3">
        <a href="/dev/json-formatter" class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl px-4 py-3 bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-colors text-center shadow-lvl1">
          <span class="text-xs font-sans font-medium text-ink">JSON Formatter</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/dev/regex-tester" class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl px-4 py-3 bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-colors text-center shadow-lvl1">
          <span class="text-xs font-sans font-medium text-ink">Regex Tester</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/dev/base64-encoder-decoder" class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl px-4 py-3 bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-colors text-center shadow-lvl1">
          <span class="text-xs font-sans font-medium text-ink">Base64 Encode/Decode</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/dev/diff-checker" class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl px-4 py-3 bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-colors text-center shadow-lvl1">
          <span class="text-xs font-sans font-medium text-ink">Diff Checker</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/dev/color-picker" class="ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl px-4 py-3 bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong transition-colors text-center shadow-lvl1">
          <span class="text-xs font-sans font-medium text-ink">Color Picker</span>
        </a>
      </div>
